# WP-021 regression-test guidance: the canonical NULL rule plus its
# text-predicate filter, isolated to a single rule so the test can
# assert violation counts deterministically.
#
# This mirrors the `n00b.s2_1.null` rule + `is_null_keyword` filter
# from the canonical `audit-rules.bnf` verbatim. The rule's filter
# resolves a match's `.text` by walking the engine's `src_text` using
# the parse tree's token line/column coordinates; under the C
# preprocessor pre-pass that buffer must be the post-preprocess source
# (WP-021), or text-predicate filters silently drop real violations.

@schema_version 1
@project naudit_preprocess_test
@description WP-021 regression fixture: the canonical NULL rule plus its is_null_keyword text-predicate filter, isolated so the test can assert deterministic violation counts under preprocessing ON and OFF.
@source_doc test/fixtures/naudit/guidance_preprocess_null.bnf
@dependencies

@filter_def is_null_keyword
    expr: arg.text_equals("NULL")
    description: Matches the literal identifier `NULL`.

@rule n00b.s2_1.null
@title NULL -> nullptr
@section section 2.1
@language c
@violation_nt provided_identifier
@filter is_null_keyword
@rationale `nullptr` is a C23 standard keyword; `NULL` is banned.
@bad return NULL;
@good return nullptr;
@guidance Replace NULL with nullptr in all expression positions.
